This paper is about developing a methodology for dialog learning in goal-oriented conversational systems. The paper proposes a language model based on quantized dialog space, which is a technique used in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to develop the language model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the proposed methodology in the context of a restaurant reservation system, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
